3. you indicate whether changes were made, and
4. you do not use the material for commercial purposes.

You may not apply legal terms or technological measures that legally restrict
others from doing anything the license permits.

For the full legal terms, please refer to the canonical license text at the
URL above.

Attribution and Provenance
--------------------------

FEMP-X is derived in part from IJADataset and includes source-code content
obtained from IJADataset.

The source-code content contained in this release, including the code stored
in the `pair_src` field of `FEMP-X.sqlite`, is distributed under the same
CC BY-NC 4.0 license as IJADataset.

This release also includes additional metadata and curation results created
for FEMP-X, including human-status metadata, LLM-based witness-generation
results, behavioral-difference categories, and generated test-source text.

When redistributing or adapting this release, please preserve attribution to:

- FEMP-X
- IJADataset
- the CC BY-NC 4.0 license

Recommended Attribution
-----------------------

A reasonable attribution should include:

- the name of the dataset: FEMP-X
- the creator/maintainer: Yoshiki Higo
- the source repository or release location
- a reference to IJADataset as an upstream source
- a link to the CC BY-NC 4.0 license
- an indication of whether changes were made

Example attribution text:

"FEMP-X, created by Yoshiki Higo, derived in part from IJADataset,
licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0. Changes were made."

